                            <comment id="14461789" author="codevise" created="Fri, 27 Jan 2006 07:49:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;now running but Exception handling disabled to go around a VerifierError (therefore not yet closed)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461717" author="codevise" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2006 11:42:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;blackdrag solved the issue with &apos;&apos;&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
in fact the error was a little bit different. Initializing a Closure &lt;br/&gt;
means always to use Reference instances. In the case above the Reference &lt;br/&gt;
  instances were prepared, but then overwritten by a careless astore &lt;br/&gt;
which sotred the Throwable there instead of using the reference. Of &lt;br/&gt;
course this means that a later access to this register gets no reference &lt;br/&gt;
but the Throwable and so the initialization of the closure inside the &lt;br/&gt;
catch block failed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But this should be fixed now... and btw, this strange workaround with &lt;br/&gt;
&quot;def local = t&quot; should also not any longer be used. It is not needed in &lt;br/&gt;
the new scoping.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;bye blackdrag&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;&apos;&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
